If the city is <fact2>45 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge</fact2>, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover the whole city?
Answer: Since it takes <fact1>92 minutes</fact1> to cover <fact2>9 miles</fact2> of the city, we can calculate the time it takes to cover 1 mile by dividing <fact1>92 minutes</fact1> by <fact2>9 miles</fact2>. This gives us 92/<fact2>9</fact2> = 10.22 minutes per mile.
To find the time it takes to cover the whole city, we need to multiply the time it takes to cover 1 mile by the total distance across the city, which is <fact2>45 miles</fact2>. This gives us 10.22 * <fact2>45</fact2> = 459 minutes.
The answer is {459}.

To find the difference in probability, we subtract the probability of rolling two <fact3>odd numbers in a row</fact3> from the probability of rolling a number greater than <fact2>3</fact2>: <fact2>0.75</fact2> - <fact3>0.3</fact3> = <fact4>0.45</fact4>. Therefore, it is 55% more likely that Hiroshi rolls a number greater than 2 than that he rolls two odd numbers in a row.
